Pre-Game Insights: Both teams are in the top three at this stage, and the winners of this game will feel very secure about their future
South Africa have lost five World Cup games in a row to New Zealand
New Zealand have had back-to-back losses to India and Australia, while South Africa have proven their only loss - to Netherlands - was an aberration
The match promises an explosive cocktail of firepower with the bat, and thrill with the ball
South Africa's pace pack has taken 44 wickets at an average and a strike rate of 23.3 and 23.5, respectively, which are the best for a team in this World Cup
Rachin Ravindra's tally of 406 runs is already the most by a New Zealander in his maiden World Cup, and he has scored 210 against spinners at a strike rate of 109
